1
00:00:00,840 --> 00:00:02,450
Let's break up.

2
00:00:03,010 --> 00:00:05,270
If we continue on

3
00:00:05,270 --> 00:00:08,310
with this fruitless relationship,

4
00:00:08,310 --> 00:00:12,630
we'll surely regret it once we're forty or fifty years old.

5
00:00:14,260 --> 00:00:19,290
To be attached to this relationship... It's a mistake.

6
00:00:20,030 --> 00:00:21,310
I'm home.

7
00:00:21,310 --> 00:00:23,780
Welcome back. I made dinner.

8
00:00:23,780 --> 00:00:25,700
- Let's eat!
- Let's eat!

9
00:00:26,890 --> 00:00:31,100
Yeah. This is how life should be.

10
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:37,410
There's nothing more to think about.

11
00:00:37,410 --> 00:00:40,310
I've obtained a normal life.

12
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:46,800
[Thirty-two]

13
00:00:50,550 --> 00:00:54,160
We're just little dots

14
00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:57,150
that were forced into this world like this.

15
00:00:57,150 --> 00:01:01,270
Helpless and lonely.

16
00:01:06,980 --> 00:01:10,900
That's why someday we search for

17
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:13,670
another dot to connect with.

18
00:01:13,670 --> 00:01:19,230
Someone that we can form a line with and live on.

19
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:34,800
♫ This life is full of ups and downs ♫

20
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:40,300
♫ But also full of expectations ♫

21
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:47,590
♫ The only hopes that make us to believe ♫

22
00:01:50,170 --> 00:01:55,720
♫ The only ropes that make us to proceed ♫

23
00:01:55,720 --> 00:02:00,990
[Life ~ Love on the Line].

24
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:04,980
[Episode 4].

25
00:02:04,980 --> 00:02:06,840
Just wait a moment.

26
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:28,190
Is this seat free?

27
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:29,830
Go ahead.

28
00:02:33,580 --> 00:02:36,950
- You're drinking alone.
- Yeah.

29
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:50,540
You don't like the smoke?

30
00:02:50,540 --> 00:02:53,600
Uh, it's not that.

31
00:02:54,550 --> 00:02:58,470
The person I was with before smoked the same kind of cigarettes.

32
00:03:01,730 --> 00:03:03,260
[Peace Light].

33
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:17,690
I'm home.

34
00:03:28,180 --> 00:03:30,090
Welcome back.

35
00:03:30,090 --> 00:03:32,430
- Would a simple dinner be all right?
- Yeah.

36
00:03:33,050 --> 00:03:36,300
Go change, you reek of cigarettes.

37
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,930
Okay.

38
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:03,790
Sorry! Give me a moment.

39
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:07,700
Is this your first time?

40
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:10,110
It's okay. I'll wait.

41
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,760
Welcome.

42
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:42,060
- Would the usual seat be okay?
- Yeah.

43
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:44,500
Understood, please go on then.

44
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:04,340
[Honoka Itou]

45
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:12,540
Hello.

46
00:05:13,470 --> 00:05:14,890
Yeah.

47
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:18,990
Not yet, I still have work to do.

48
00:05:20,020 --> 00:05:23,150
Sorry. Go to bed without me.

49
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,970
Goodnight.

50
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:13,290
I don't have to worry about him

51
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:16,060
not being there when I wake up.

52
00:06:20,590 --> 00:06:24,820
It's fine like this...

53
00:06:44,190 --> 00:06:47,170
All right, I'm going to head home.

54
00:06:53,970 --> 00:06:58,110
I'm truly sorry, but it's closing time.

55
00:06:58,110 --> 00:06:59,880
Sorry.

56
00:08:03,090 --> 00:08:04,990
What are you doing?

57
00:08:04,990 --> 00:08:08,900
I don't know, I just felt like sitting.

58
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:12,390
What about you?

59
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:15,740
I'm heading to the convenience store just to get a breath of air.

60
00:08:15,740 --> 00:08:17,370
I see.

61
00:08:20,570 --> 00:08:24,540
Akira! Hurry up!

62
00:08:26,110 --> 00:08:29,910
Come on, hurry up!

63
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:33,020
Here we go. Ready!

64
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:34,510
Fight!

65
00:08:36,050 --> 00:08:39,510
More!

66
00:08:39,510 --> 00:08:41,400
Faster!

67
00:08:42,770 --> 00:08:44,800
More!

68
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:49,830
Time out, time out!

69
00:08:49,830 --> 00:08:52,280
I'm seriously at my limit!

70
00:08:58,790 --> 00:09:01,270
Let's go back and drink some beer!

71
00:09:01,270 --> 00:09:02,950
That sounds great.

72
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,200
Hand me the bag.

73
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,720
Thank you.

74
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:41,510
[I'm worried because it's getting late.]
[Is it still going to take more time?]

75
00:09:43,210 --> 00:09:46,280
I need to stand up.

76
00:09:51,870 --> 00:09:55,610
If I don't stand up, the day will break.

77
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:23,990
On that day...

78
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:26,370
amidst the sunrise,

79
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:29,800
I realized something.

80
00:10:31,930 --> 00:10:36,380
That I loved Yuki too much.

81
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:47,470
After realizing that, I put a stop to it.

82
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:54,050
I shouldn't love him anymore than this.

83
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:03,030
What's wrong?

84
00:12:11,350 --> 00:12:14,220
There's someone that you like...

85
00:12:14,220 --> 00:12:16,720
and it's a man.

86
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:28,820
You're the worst!

87
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:35,720
I'm truly sorry.

88
00:12:36,330 --> 00:12:39,250
That's not something you can get off with just apologizing for!

89
00:12:40,450 --> 00:12:42,040
I'm sorry...

90
00:12:43,710 --> 00:12:48,400
In the end, you just didn't want to hurt yourself. Right?

91
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:52,770
So you just decided how others should feel!

92
00:13:06,090 --> 00:13:08,600
You really like him...

93
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:24,360
Ugh...

94
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:33,060
Even when I wish for it, in the end there's nothing I can reach.

95
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:49,360
[Thirty-three]

96
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:52,490
[Divorce registration papers, Akira Itou, Honoka Itou]

97
00:13:56,070 --> 00:13:59,720
[Akira Itou]

98
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:04,030
They just accepted it.

99
00:14:05,460 --> 00:14:07,460
Are we really doing that?

100
00:14:07,460 --> 00:14:10,390
We're doing it, a divorce banquet!

101
00:14:10,390 --> 00:14:14,960
We're going to rent a hotel suite so I can complain to all my friends!

102
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:17,140
Oh, okay.

103
00:14:17,140 --> 00:14:21,250
I'm going to pass the bill to you. The settlement money will be separate!

104
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:23,460
Be prepared!

105
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:35,320
Sorry for the wait!

106
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:37,350
Well then, let's continue.

107
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:42,610
Well, how about the color of this one and this one?

108
00:14:42,610 --> 00:14:44,030
- Yes!
- Yes!

109
00:14:44,030 --> 00:14:46,260
I'm glad to hear that!

110
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:58,460
Hello, Mother?

111
00:14:58,460 --> 00:15:00,970
I'm heading home right now.

112
00:15:00,970 --> 00:15:03,690
There's something I want to talk to you about.

113
00:15:03,690 --> 00:15:07,120
That's fine, but right now we're in a pinch!

114
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:09,840
Just now, your older sister came home.

115
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:12,570
[Itou]

116
00:15:12,570 --> 00:15:16,770
- Let us in!
- I can't!
- I want to talk to you about it inside.

117
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,940
I told you, no!

118
00:15:18,940 --> 00:15:20,920
You're so selfish!

119
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,980
Auntie I... Auntie I...

120
00:15:22,980 --> 00:15:28,040
I understand that this is a really sensitive topic but don't get angry.

121
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:32,970
- Hitomi, we can quietly sort this out. Right?
- Just shut up, you keep uttering without shame.

122
00:15:32,970 --> 00:15:35,930
In any case, I've already decided!

123
00:15:35,930 --> 00:15:38,360
What did you just say?

124
00:15:40,470 --> 00:15:42,250
Akira!

125
00:15:43,260 --> 00:15:47,100
Um, what's going on here?

126
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:53,110
An international marriage?

127
00:15:56,460 --> 00:15:58,720
Hitomi is just feeling excited, that's all.

128
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:00,970
That's not it!

129
00:16:00,970 --> 00:16:04,310
Hassan and I really love each other!

130
00:16:04,310 --> 00:16:07,330
- I won't accept it.
- Huh!?

131
00:16:07,330 --> 00:16:10,070
You've always been like that.

132
00:16:10,070 --> 00:16:12,800
You always act without thinking.

133
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:16,490
It's too late to regret it once you've already failed!

134
00:16:16,490 --> 00:16:20,900
You're no longer of an age where youthful enthusiasm can accomplish anything.

135
00:16:22,430 --> 00:16:26,000
We're no longer of an age where youthful enthusiasm can accomplish anything.

136
00:16:27,550 --> 00:16:30,590
Why are you deciding that we're going to fail!

137
00:16:30,590 --> 00:16:34,850
I never told you that you can't get married!

138
00:16:34,850 --> 00:16:40,450
But please, bring a normal person!

139
00:16:40,450 --> 00:16:44,600
- You'll regret it when you're forty or fifty!
- Not that again!

140
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,830
What do you know about Hassan!?

141
00:16:46,830 --> 00:16:49,670
I don't know anything, that's why I'm saying it!

142
00:16:49,670 --> 00:16:53,670
If you have an international marriage and get a divorce so soon,

143
00:16:53,670 --> 00:16:56,210
do you know what the neighbors will say!

144
00:16:56,210 --> 00:16:59,640
Think of it from my position!

145
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:03,040
A normal happiness is fine!

146
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:07,370
Marriage is something between the two families!

147
00:17:07,370 --> 00:17:10,540
You should learn from Akira!

148
00:17:10,540 --> 00:17:12,990
He went to a local university,

149
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:17,060
got a job, and had a normal marriage. Right?

150
00:17:17,690 --> 00:17:22,130
Why can't you live normally like Akira?

151
00:17:22,130 --> 00:17:25,600
- Maybe there's—
- Stop it already!

152
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:32,160
Normal, normal, normal! What the hell is normal!?

153
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:34,630
I'm tired of all this!

154
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:39,890
Why do they have to break up even though they love each other?

155
00:17:41,890 --> 00:17:44,060
Akira?

156
00:17:44,060 --> 00:17:46,890
I've been frantically trying to live normally.

157
00:17:46,890 --> 00:17:50,180
I read people's faces in order to not stray from the norm.

158
00:17:50,180 --> 00:17:52,660
In order to not fail! That's how I've lived!

159
00:17:52,660 --> 00:17:58,270
I act in a way so that I would be accepted by those around me!

160
00:17:58,270 --> 00:18:02,530
But I wasn't able to become happy!

161
00:18:04,590 --> 00:18:07,030
But you have Honoka...

162
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:09,130
We got divorced.

163
00:18:09,130 --> 00:18:10,650
Huh?

164
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:16,450
There's someone that I just can't forget.

165
00:18:17,450 --> 00:18:20,480
What are you saying, Akira?

166
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,990
I...

167
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,850
I love Yuki after all.

168
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:35,290
Yuki Nishi, do you remember him?

169
00:18:37,630 --> 00:18:39,670
Yuki Nishi...

170
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:45,210
Nishi-kun?

171
00:18:45,910 --> 00:18:48,220
That friend of yours!?

172
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:52,360
You might not be able to accept it so easily, but

173
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:56,570
I truly loved Yuki.

174
00:18:57,130 --> 00:18:59,310
Only when I was with him

175
00:18:59,310 --> 00:19:01,700
was I truly able to be myself.

176
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:05,280
I was truly happy.

177
00:19:11,670 --> 00:19:16,120
I was stupid and weak.

178
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:18,470
I was held down by trying to be normal.

179
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:22,250
And I let go of

180
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:24,710
the person that I truly loved.

181
00:19:26,970 --> 00:19:31,620
So, someone who's living honestly to their own feelings like Big Sis...

182
00:19:31,620 --> 00:19:34,500
I want her to be happy!

183
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:36,860
Accept it!

184
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:42,660
Compared to love between men, an international relationship is normal. Right!?

185
00:19:49,150 --> 00:19:50,840
Big Sis,

186
00:19:53,370 --> 00:19:55,580
I support you.

187
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:58,650
Akira...

188
00:20:00,910 --> 00:20:02,730
Akira!

189
00:20:07,260 --> 00:20:12,240
Live proudly!

190
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:18,190
♫ Be loved, be wanted ♫

191
00:20:18,190 --> 00:20:22,270
♫ Hear your name called ♫

192
00:20:22,270 --> 00:20:26,440
Thank you.

193
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:29,310
Thank you, Mr. Akira!

194
00:20:29,310 --> 00:20:35,510
♫ I finally do, I finally do ♫

195
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:41,560
[Yuki Nishi]

196
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:45,420
Could it be that he's with someone else already?

197
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:51,020
No, don't think about that!

198
00:20:54,130 --> 00:21:02,290
The number you have called is no longer in use.

199
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:12,200
Please try again.

200
00:21:13,330 --> 00:21:15,160
♫ The watch's ♫

201
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:23,490
♫ Needle continues to tick-tock, moving forward ♫

202
00:21:25,330 --> 00:21:29,490
That's great! The two of us could ride a camel,

203
00:21:29,490 --> 00:21:31,860
and fight mosnters and stuff.

204
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:42,120
♫ I'm by myself again, standing alone ♫

205
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:49,430
Excuse me, is there are person named Yuki Nishi there?

206
00:21:49,430 --> 00:21:51,650
Yuki Nishi?

207
00:21:51,650 --> 00:21:53,490
Please hold on a moment.

208
00:21:53,490 --> 00:21:54,850
Okay.

209
00:21:58,060 --> 00:21:59,950
Thank you for waiting.

210
00:21:59,950 --> 00:22:04,270
He's no longer in our production staff.

211
00:22:04,270 --> 00:22:06,770
I'm truly sorry!

212
00:22:06,770 --> 00:22:10,000
Okay, thank you anyway.

213
00:22:13,950 --> 00:22:16,990
We worked with Mr. Nishi through his office,

214
00:22:16,990 --> 00:22:20,300
so I have never contacted him directly before.

215
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:23,210
Is that so? Thank you then.

216
00:22:23,210 --> 00:22:25,030
Pardon the sudden call.

217
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:34,530
Sorry, that would be personal information.

218
00:22:34,530 --> 00:22:37,810
So long as you're not a family member, then...

219
00:22:37,810 --> 00:22:41,380
Okay, thank you anyway...

220
00:23:20,970 --> 00:23:25,010
[Thirty-six]

221
00:23:25,010 --> 00:23:29,930
Surely Yuki is somewhere that I don't know about,

222
00:23:29,930 --> 00:23:34,630
and he's probably getting along with someone else that's not me.

223
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:44,140
[Alaska Fairbanks Aurora]

224
00:24:13,370 --> 00:24:16,100
Lately, Fairbanks has been snowing a lot, but

225
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:20,520
it's finally cleared up. You're quite lucky!

226
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:21,880
Is that so?

227
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:25,580
Well, as long as nothing unexpected comes along, you should be able to see it!

228
00:24:25,580 --> 00:24:27,400
The aurora!

229
00:24:33,070 --> 00:24:36,620
See! It's so pretty!

230
00:24:38,060 --> 00:24:41,490
- Today is a great day!
- That's amazing!

231
00:24:41,490 --> 00:24:43,570
There's a better place over there.

232
00:24:43,570 --> 00:24:47,400
Please watch your step!

233
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:49,530
It's great, isn't it?

234
00:24:49,530 --> 00:24:51,690
It's so amazing!

235
00:24:51,690 --> 00:24:54,180
You're all very lucky!

236
00:24:54,180 --> 00:24:58,880
It's like there are lines formed in the sky.

237
00:25:20,530 --> 00:25:23,330
Sorry for the wait!

238
00:25:24,290 --> 00:25:26,680
You're late!

239
00:25:36,130 --> 00:25:39,520
I told you that it would be pretty!

240
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:43,640
Let's hurry and go.

241
00:25:45,950 --> 00:25:48,020
It's so cold!

242
00:26:12,830 --> 00:26:14,590
Sorry about that!

243
00:26:33,380 --> 00:26:35,100
Yuki!

244
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:45,160
I love you!

245
00:27:04,300 --> 00:27:06,360
I love you!

246
00:27:06,360 --> 00:27:08,810
- Let go!
- I won't let go!

247
00:27:08,810 --> 00:27:12,240
- Let go of me!
- I don't want to!

248
00:27:13,500 --> 00:27:17,070
I won't ever run away again!

249
00:27:26,170 --> 00:27:30,740
I wanted the two of us to come here together...

250
00:27:31,630 --> 00:27:36,690
I can't... It's impossible for me...

251
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:41,510
I tried so many times to give up...

252
00:27:44,140 --> 00:27:45,730
Sorry...

253
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:49,000
I put you through all that pain...

254
00:27:50,300 --> 00:27:55,720
I really tried, so many times.

255
00:27:56,940 --> 00:28:00,000
I tried so many times to give up on you!

256
00:28:01,450 --> 00:28:02,990
I'm sorry...

257
00:28:04,010 --> 00:28:05,890
I'm sorry!

258
00:28:07,130 --> 00:28:09,560
But it was impossible!

259
00:28:11,610 --> 00:28:13,910
I couldn't do it this whole time!

260
00:28:18,050 --> 00:28:21,130
I thought that I could put an end to it.

261
00:28:25,380 --> 00:28:31,130
So I came here and tried to

262
00:28:31,130 --> 00:28:33,510
forget about you, Akira.

263
00:28:36,700 --> 00:28:38,330
I'm sorry.

264
00:28:40,120 --> 00:28:41,800
It's all...

265
00:28:43,030 --> 00:28:45,880
It's all my fault.

266
00:28:47,290 --> 00:28:48,870
I'm sorry!

267
00:29:07,510 --> 00:29:10,610
Promise me something.

268
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:13,930
I will.

269
00:29:13,930 --> 00:29:15,990
Promise me, truly.

270
00:29:15,990 --> 00:29:17,670
I promise.

271
00:29:19,410 --> 00:29:22,880
I'll make you even a hundred or a thousand promises.

272
00:29:24,170 --> 00:29:26,440
I promise you, Yuki.

273
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:30,130
Just one is fine.

